## 7. Conclusions

This implementation successfully demonstrates a self-pruning neural network that:

- Achieves approximately **56.7% test accuracy** on CIFAR-10 using a flat MLP — competitive for this architecture class
- Trains stably across all three λ values with no divergence or accuracy collapse
- Applies hard pruning after training with **zero accuracy drop**, confirming the gates correctly identify redundant connections
- Produces clean visualisations of gate distributions and training dynamics

The learnable gate mechanism is a principled, gradient-based alternative to traditional pruning, and the results validate that it can be trained end-to-end alongside classification without compromising accuracy.
